Name: Date
Description: Date of ArrivalTime. For example: 2020-12-31

Name: ParentOrderID
Description: Unique identifier per algo run

Name: Symbol
Description: Currency pair of ParentOrderID. For example:  EURUSD

Name: TradeCurrency
Description: Denomination currency for OrderQuantity

Name: Side
Description: Buy (B) or Sell (S). Buy or sell applies to currency pair (Symbol) in FX market convention, not to TradeCurrency.  For example, if Symbol is provided as EURUSD,  buys always means buying EUR and selling USD

Name: LegSymbols
Description: All currency pairs which have been traded to execute this ParentOrderID. This is relevant for multi-leg execution. For example, where AUDNOK is traded through 3 legs:  AUDUSD, EURNOK and EURUSD

Name: Trader
Description: The name of  a trader associated with this ParentOrderID

Name: Account
Description: Name of the underlying client this ParentOrderID executed on behalf of

Name: SubAccount
Description: SubAccount associated with this ParentOrderID

Name: AlgoName
Description: AlgoName such as  "TWAP", "Shortfall", "Tiger" (normally marketing name under which an algo is sold by AlgoVendor)

Name: LP
Description: AlgoVendor: institution responsible for overall algo execution

Name: TimeZoneArrive
Description: Trading time zone of the ArrivalTime: "London" (07:00-15:00 GMT), "NewYork" (15:00-22:00 GMT) and "Asia" (22:00-07:00 GMT)

Name: HourArrive
Description: Hour of the ArrivalTime, GMT, 0 to 23. "0"  for ArrivalTime between 00:00 and 00:59:59, "1" for  ArrivalTime between 01:00 and 01:59:59 etc

Name: TimeZoneEnd
Description: Trading time zone of the LastTime: "London" (07:00-15:00 GMT), "NewYork" (15:00-22:00 GMT) and "Asia" (22:00-07:00 GMT)

Name: HourEnd
Description: Hour of the LastTime, GMT, 0 to 23. "0"  for LastTime between 00:00 and 00:59:59, "1" for  LastTime between 01:00 and 01:59:59 etc

Name: G10EM
Description: G10 or EM currency pair. G10 currency is EUR,USD,JPY,GBP,AUD,NZD,CAD,NOK,SEK,CHF.  If at least one currency in currency pair is not G10 currency then currency pair is classified as EM, otherwise it is G10

Name: TradeSizeBucketUSDM
Description: Translation of TradeQuantityUSD into USD size bucket in human readable format like 0-50, 50-100 etc.  0-50 means algo TradeQuantityUSD is between 0 and $50mil etc

Name: OrderQuantity
Description: Total  quantity ordered. For example: 10,000,000. In units of TradeCurrency. For ParentOrderID with multiple order quantities (amends) only the last ordered quantity is reported.

Name: AvgChildOrderQuantityUSD
Description: Average Size of Child Order in USD

Name: OrderQuantityUSD
Description: USD Equivalent of OrderQuantity

Name: TradeQuantityUSD
Description: USD Equivalent of TradeQuantity

Name: TradeQuantity
Description: TradeQuantity in TradeCurrency

Name: RemainQuantity
Description: Amount which is not executed (in TradeCurrency)

Name: ArrivalTime
Description: Time (GMT) when the execution desk starts to execute the order.

Name: ArrivalPrice
Description: The Tradefeedr mid-price of the Symbol at the time immediately preceding the ArrivalTime. This is used for ArrivalMidPerfBPS.

Name: TWAPPrice
Description: Time Weighted Average Price of Symbol during algo execution

Name: LastTime
Description: The time the algo execution is done. Unless specific instruction is provided by AlgoVendor it is the time of the last fill.

Name: LastPrice
Description: Last mid price for Symbol observed at LastTime. The RemainQuantity is marked to market at LastPrice and is used to calculate ArrivalMidPerfRemainNetBPS

Name: NumChildEvents
Description: Total Number of Child Events in ParentOrderID. The events include child order execution (fills), rejects and order placement by AlgoVendor

Name: NumParentEvents
Description: Total Number of Parent Events in ParentOrderID. The events include Parent Order Events. There should be at least one per ParentOrderID describing initial algo orders. Parent events represent all user instructions delivered to AlgoVendor (LP) such as LimitPrice changes, Algo Urgency changes, Order Size Changes, Stop and Start etc.

Name: CurrencyPositions
Description: Decomposition of all child order executions into positions by currency. For example {‘EUR’: -1000, “USD”: 1100}. Normally only useful for multi-leg algo where for example AUDNOK is executed through AUDUSD, EURNOK and EURUSD legs and the resulting position will contain two main target currencies in the cross (AUD and NOK in this case).

Name: Duration
Description: Order Duration in seconds.

Name: TradeIntensity
Description: Trading intensity per ParentOrderID: average speed of execution in USD traded per minute. Equals to TradeQuantityUSD/ (Duration/60)

Name: OrderIntensity
Description: Trading intensity per ParentOrderID based on OrderQuantityUSD.  Average speed of execution in USD traded per minute. Equals to OrderQuantityUSD/ (Duration/60)

Name: RiskTransferPrice
Description: Risk Transfer Price at ArrivalTime and for OrderQuantity for this order as submitted by AlgoVendor

Name: PrincipalMid
Description: PrincipalMid at ArrivalTime for this order as submitted by AlgoVendor

Name: DailyVolatilityPct
Description: Volatility forecast for the execution day. Expressed as annualised volatility of Symbol in percentage points. For example, 10.5% is reported as 10.5.

Name: ArrivalVolatilityPct
Description: Volatility as measured at the ArrivalTime. Based on intraday volatility model. Expressed as annualized volatility of Symbol in percentage points. For example 10.5% is reported as 10.5.

Name: SpreadPaidPMChildOrders
Description: TradeQuantityUSD-weighted average spread paid of child fills. For each child fill the spread paid is the difference between mid price and executed price expressed in $/m (100xbasis point) and adjusted for Side. Positive number means buying above the mid and selling below. Expressed in $/m.

Name: AllInPrice
Description:
Effective overall rate at which ParentOrderID was executed. For single leg executions it is TradeQuantityUSD-weighted-average Price over all child fills.
For multi-leg order each execution is split into individual currencies. Then effective currency balances of all executions are aggregated. Finally, effective rate is calculated as a ratio of the balance of target currencies. For example if target Symbol is AUDNOK and the AUD balance is 1m and NOK balance is 6m then the effective execution rate would be 6m/1m = 6.

Name: AllInNetPrice
Description: Net effective overall rate at which ParentOrderID was executed. It is AllInPrice adjusted for algo provider fees. It is calculated by Tradefeedr from NetPrices of child orders in the same way as AllInPrice. Should be above AllInPrice for Side=B and below AllInPrice for Side=S with the difference being execution fees

Name: ExecutionScore
Description: TradeQuantityUSD-Weighed-Average Scores of Individual Child Orders. Execution Scores  of individual child fills are calculated as rank-percentile of Price against the distribution of mid-price during algo execution.  It is the number between 0 and 100. For example, buy at the low of range would get a rank of 100 and buy at the high the price range would get a rank of 0 (reverse for sell order).

Name: ReversalScore
Description: TradeQuantityUSD-Weighed-Average Reversal Scores of Individual Child Orders. Reversal Scores of individual child fills are calculated as rank percentiles of Price against the distribution of mid-price post algo execution.  It is a number between 0 and 100. For example, buy at the low of range would get a rank of 100 and buy at the high the price range would get a rank of 0 (reverse for sell order).

Name: RiskTransferCostReportedPM
Description: Risk transfer cost as reported by AlgoVendor. If AlgoVendor does not submit this information, None is returned.  Expressed in $/m (100 x basis point)

Name: RiskTransferCostStaticPM
Description: Risk trader cost as submitted by Tradefeedr client. Can be missing/None if it was not provided by the Tradefeedr client. Expressed in $/m (100 x basis point)

Name: RiskTransferCostVolBumpPM
Description: RiskTransferCostStaticPM adjusted for volatility level to reflect current market trading conditions. Expressed in $/m (100 x basis point)

Name: RiskTransferCostModelPM
Description: Tradefeedr estimated risk transfer cost, average level per symbol per trading day.  Expressed in $/m (100xbasis point). Mainly used to calibrate user provided RiskTransferCostStaticPM

Name: RiskTransferCostTradefeedrPM
Description: Tradefeedr estimated risk transfer cost  for ParentOrderID.  Expressed in $/m (100xbasis point).

Name: AssumedRisk
Description: Cumulative volatility of the market during ParentOrderID. Based on Tradefeedr intraday volatility model. Volatility is estimated for each minute and integrated over the duration of the algo. Expressed in basis points.

Name: ArrivalMidPerfTradeBPS
Description: Percentage Difference between ArrivalPrice (arrival mid) and AllInPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means out-performance of mid price (buying below the ArrivalPrice and selling above). Expressed in basis points.

Name: ArrivalMidPerfRemainBPS
Description: Market move during algo execution adjusted by Side. When it is negative the market moved in the direction of trading making subsequent purchases more costly (e.g. market moving up when algo was buying). This is used to adjust algo for un-executed amounts.   Expressed in basis points.

Name: ArrivalMidPerfBPS
Description: Total algo performance to ArrivalPrice (arrival mid). Positive number means out-performance (buying below mid, selling below mid). Weighted average of ArrivalMidPerfTradeBPS and ArrivalMidPerfRemainBPS with weights being proportional to TradeQuantity and RemainQuantity.  Expressed in basis points.

Name: TWAPMidPerfBPS
Description: Percentage difference between AllInPrice and TWAPPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means out-performance of TWAPPrice (buying below the TWAPPrice and selling above TWAPPrice). Expressed in basis points

Name: ArrivalMidPerfNetBPS
Description: Net total algo performance to ArrivalPrice (arrival mid).  Positive in out-performance (buying below mid, selling below mid). When aggregated it is weighted average of ArrivalMidPerfTradeNetBPS and ArrivalMidPerfRemainNetBPS with weights being proportional to TradeQuantity and RemainQuantity.  Expressed in basis points

Name: ArrivalMidPerfTradeNetBPS
Description: Performance To Arrival Mid. Percentage Difference between ArrivalPrice and AllInNetPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means out-performance of mid price (buying below the ArrivalPrice and selling above. Expressed in basis points.

Name: ArrivalMidPerfRemainNetBPS
Description: Market move during algo execution adjusted to the Side. When it is negative the market moved in the direction of trading making subsequent purchases more costly (e.g. market moving up when algo was buying). This is used to adjust algo for un-executed amounts.

Name: TWAPMidPerfNetBPS
Description: Percentage difference between AllInNetPrice and TWAPPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means outperformance of TWAPPrice (buying below the TWAPPrice and selling above TWAPPrice). Expressed in basis points

Name: SlippageToArrivalMidTradePM
Description: SlippageToArrivalMidTradePM. Percentage difference between ArrivalPrice and AllInPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means underperformance of mid price (buying above the ArrivalPrice and selling below. Expressed in $/m (100 x Basis Point or 10,000 percent)

Name: SlippageToArrivalMidRemainPM
Description: SlippageToArrivalMidRemainPM. Market move during algo execution adjusted to the Side. This is used to adjust algo for un-executed amounts.

Name: SlippageToArrivalMidPM
Description: SlippageToArrivalMid (Positive in underperformance, negative is out-performance). Total slippage to arrival mid. Weighted average of SlippageToArrivalMidTradePM and SlippageToArrivalMidRemainPM with wights proportional to TradeQuantity and RemainQuantity.  Expressed in $/m (100 x Basis Point or 10,000 percent)

Name: SlippageToTWAPMidPM
Description: Percentage Difference between Algo Effective Execution Price (AllInPrice) and TWAPPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means underperformance of TWAPPrice (buying above the TWAPPrice and selling below TWAPPrice). Expressed in $/m (100 x Basis Point or 10,000 percent)

Name: SlippageToArrivalMidNetPM
Description: SlippageToArrivalMid (Positive in underperformance, negative is out-performance). Total slippage to arrival mid. Weighted average of SlippageToArrivalMidTradePM and SlippageToArrivalMidRemainPM with weights being proportional to TradeQuantity and RemainQuantity.  Expressed in $/m (100 x Basis Point)

Name: SlippageToArrivalMidTradeNetPM
Description: SlippageToArrivalMidTradePM. Percentage Difference between ArrivalPrice and AllInPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means underperformance of mid price (buying above the ArrivalPrice and selling below. Expressed in $/m (100 x Basis Point)

Name: SlippageToArrivalMidRemainNetPM
Description: SlippageToArrivalMidRemainPM. Market move during algo execution adjusted to the Side. This is used to adjust algo for non-executed amounts.

Name: SlippageToTWAPMidNetPM
Description: Percentage Difference between AllInNetPrice and TWAPPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means net under-performance of TWAPPrice (buying above the TWAPPrice and selling below TWAPPrice). Expressed in $/m (100 x Basis Point)

Name: SubmissionTime
Description: Time (GMT) when the order arrives to the execution desk.

Name: SubmissionPrice
Description: The Tradefeedr mid-price of the Symbol at the time immediately preceding the SubmissionTime. This is used for SubmissionMidPerfBPS.

Name: FirstFillTime
Description: Time (GMT) when the the first order is executed.

Name: FirstFillPrice
Description: The Tradefeedr mid-price of the Symbol at the time immediately preceding the FirstFillTime. This is used for FirstFillMidPerfBPS.

Name: SubmissionMidPerfBPS
Description: Total algo performance to SubmissionPrice. Positive number means out-performance (buying below mid, selling below mid). Weighted average of SubmissionMidPerfTradeBPS and SubmissionMidPerfRemainBPS with weights being proportional to TradeQuantity and RemainQuantity. Expressed in basis points.

Name: SubmissionMidPerfTradeBPS
Description: Percentage Difference between SubmissionPrice  and AllInPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means out-performance of mid price (buying below the SubmissionPrice  and selling above). Expressed in basis points.

Name: SubmissionMidPerfRemainBPS
Description: Market move during algo execution adjusted by Side. When it is negative the market moved in the direction of trading making subsequent purchases more costly (e.g. market moving up when algo was buying). This is used to adjust algo for un-executed amounts. Expressed in basis points.

Name: SubmissionMidPerfNetBPS
Description: Net of fees version of SubmissionMidPerfBPS

Name: SubmissionMidPerfTradeNetBPS
Description: Net of fees version of SubmissionMidPerfTradeBPS

Name: SubmissionMidPerfRemainNetBPS
Description: Net of fees (client price) version of SubmissionMidPerfRemainBPS

Name: FirstFillMidPerfBPS
Description: Total algo performance to FirstFillPrice. Positive number means out-performance (buying below mid, selling below mid). Weighted average of FirstFillMidPerfTradeBPS and FirstFillMidPerfRemainBPS with weights being proportional to TradeQuantity and RemainQuantity. Expressed in basis points.

Name: FirstFillMidPerfTradeBPS
Description: Percentage Difference between FirstFillPrice and AllInPrice. Adjusted for Side. Positive number means out-performance of mid price (buying below the SubmissionPriceÂ  and selling above). Expressed in basis points.

Name: FirstFillMidPerfRemainBPS
Description: Market move during algo execution adjusted by Side. When it is negative the market moved in the direction of trading making subsequent purchases more costly (e.g. market moving up when algo was buying). This is used to adjust algo for un-executed amounts.Expressed in basis points.

Name: FirstFillMidPerfNetBPS
Description: Net of fees version of FirstFillMidPerfBPS

Name: FirstFillMidPerfTradeNetBPS
Description: Net of fees version of FirstFillMidPerfTradeBPS

Name: FirstFillMidPerfRemainNetBPS
Description: Net of fees version of FirstFillMidPerfRemainBPS
